<div class="row">
	<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
		<h2>Create a line chart</h2>
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4">
			<p>Upload a file containing 2 or more tab-separated columns, where the first column lists the x-values and the other columns list the y values for your data series (1 column per series).</p>
			<p>To configure the chart title, labels and unit of measurement, you may add their values to the top of your file like this:</p>
			<code>#title=My amazing line chart</code><br/>
			<code>#x-axis=Days</code><br/>
			<code>#y-axis=Dollars</code><br/>
			<code>#y-series=Week 1,Week 2</code><br/>
			<code>1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5</code><br/>
			<code>2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6</code><br/>
			<code>...</code>
			<%= simple_form_for :line, url: "/charts/display_line", :html => { :multipart => true }, :remote => true do |form| %>
			  <br/>Select base color: <%= form.text_field :color, :value => '#317777' %><br/>
			  Select data file: <%= form.file_field :data %><br/>
			  <%= form.submit 'Draw the line', :class => 'btn btn-primary' %>
			<% end  %>
		</div>
		<div id="line" class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-8 chart-display"></div>
	</div>
</div>
